	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f104196606278829>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>The Cleric Soloers Guide - Levels 40 to 58</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jan 7th 2:01 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32655><span id= >AngryGnome the Malevolent</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I've been soloing from the beginning.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have a level 58 high elven cleric.  My AC is only 925 b/c I'm not in an uber guild and I haven't gone after armor which requires an uber guild to obtain.  My wisdom is 255.  Str, Sta, and Agi are approx 100.  Cha and Sta are mid-80s.  Dex gets up over 205 with Yaulp V.  Hps fully buffed are 2600.<br><br>Before reading this guide, please note the following:<br><br>1)  Get your wis over 200 as soon as possible.<br>2)  Max out 1 hb, bash, offense, defense, alteration, conjuration and evocation.<br>3)  Get used to the idea that you'll be soloing mostly in Lower Guk, Dreadlands, Burning Woods, and Karnor's Castle up until you hit 56, at which point your life will totally change (details below), and you'll be able to go virtually anywhere. Luclin, Velious, Faydwer and Odus aren't that great for clerics 40 and up.  Kunark is the best continent for us.<br>4)  Learn how to use root/atone to clear aggro from adds.<br>5)  When soloing, be sure to use ALL hp/ac buffs in your arsenal.  You'll get your money back for the gems simply by the plat that drops off the mobs.<br><br>Levels 40 to 45 - your best bet is root/nuking plaguebone skeletons and some of the other lower level undead mobs in the Dreadlands.  When they get low on hps, you can melee as mana permits.  When you get down to 2 bubbles of life, however, you should root the mob, back up and heal yourself.  There is an undead ruin in the NE corner of the zone.  Undead mobs can be single pulled from this ruin.  There is a single plaguebone skeleton that spawns on the zone wall just north of this ruin, which is where I recommend you start.  At level 40, any undead other than a plaguebone in this area will kill you.  Fortunately, you can single pull all undead mobs in this area.  Should you get an add, root it, move away from it, and cast atone on the mob.  This has about a 50% chance to clear all aggro just like the enchanter spell &quot;mem blur.&quot;  You'll be able to tell if it worked b/c the mob will turn away from you.  If it fails, simply repeat.<br><br>The other option for clerics at this level is the zone-in to the undead side of Lower Guk.  Same deal - root and nuke.  Stay near zone-in.  Tip for Guk - keep good faction with frogs on the Live side.<br><br>Levels 45 to 50 - More options for targets are available to you now at the ruin in the NE corner of Dreadlands as you can now kill many more of the undead mobs that spawn there.  In addition, you can more safely kill many of the undead that spawn near the wizzy spire at the far west end of the zone.  Many of the live mobs roaming around are now viable targets for your normal nukes as well.<br><br>I recommend not soloing in Lower Guk again until 56 b/c the entrance mob exp isn't that great anymore at these levels, and aggro issues further in will make it too difficult.  However, if any cleric out there levels 45 to 56 has found a way to solo in Lower Guk with reasonable safety, I'd love to hear about it.  Invis to undead and go camp assassin perhaps?<br><br>Levels 50 to 55 - Many of the DL mobs still give exp, but it's really time to move to Burning Woods, especially after 52 when you get Epitaph of Life, your undead DoT.  Zone into BW from DL and run straight north.  There is very little pathing in this area, so you won't be attacked.  When you find the road, follow it all the way to the giant fort.  Again, it is easy to avoid mobs on the way.  To the right of the giant fort (east), there is an undead ruin.  Pull anything except Greater Warbones and Tatterback Gorillas.  Tatterback Apes, plaguebones, spurbones, etc are all great exp.  At 54 and 55, you can even use reckoning to kill the giants in the fort fairly effectively.<br><br>If you have the means to breath underwater, you can go into Karnor's Castle and fight while submerged.  Zone in, go to left moat, and follow the wall all the way to the back.  Jump in!  There is an underwater nook back there that is easy to single pull to.  It's more difficult than BW, but a nice change of pace.  And NO trains.<br><br>Levels 56 to 58 - At this point, everything changes.  With your new Yaulp, you regenerate mana at the same rate standing as you do sitting down.  You are hasted 25%, attack goes up by 40 and dex by 75.  Your new hammer is 14/18 plus stats and procs a 150 DD.  WHY did you get these spells?  So you can MELEE.  That's right, no more sitting and medding for you.  You can take aggro from a monk sometimes.  You can farm effectively in lower level dungeons for the very first time.  You can go toe to toe with the Dog Captain in KC and win. You can go back to Lower Guk, get great exp and kill almost anything in the dungeon.  It's easy for you to single pull in most areas of Norrath.  Oh sure, you can use judgement and nuke em to death quickly (925 nuke without bonuses), but that's just not as fun as beating the hell out of em.  You don't have to root and nuke, you don't have to kite, you can go toe to toe and kick some ass.  Here's how:<br><br>Root your target.  Cast Mark of Retribution on it. Cast celestial healing on yourself.  Either rush the mob, or nuke it to break root so it will come to you.  Hit Yaulp V and celestial heal as needed.  Summon your hammer pet.  Beat the piss out of the mob.  Bash often.  You can cast celestial heal, yaulp V and your hammer pet without being interrupted very often, even if under attack.  You can eliminate some of these spells as you see fit depending on the difficulty of the mob.<br><br>At level 58, I can roam Guk using improved invis, find blues and kill one right after another over and over again staying at full mana b/c I don't even have to summon the hammer pet or use mark of retribution to kill them.  I just melee with my summoned hammer and heal.  I can hold the RCY in KC all by myself with KEI.  I'm just scratching the surface - there are many places you can go and do really well solo at this point.  You're a cleric, so it's kinda like having 30,000 hit points.  If you get in trouble, you just root, back up and CH yourself.  Maybe sit down and med for a few seconds, and go right back in there.  And if they piss you off, finish em off with nukes before they can say oops.<br><br>Hope this helps someone.  If you ever stop by Bertoxxulous, say hi to Seint.  I'll be happy to personally demonstrate any of the tactics I have described here for ya.  Enjoy!</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
